# spine.px — Event Spine topology (v3 dataflow)
#
# This file defines the COMPLETE queue topology for pares-radix.
# It is the single source of truth for how data flows through the system.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PluresDB IS the router. Writing to a queue IS routing.
# The graph runs to quiescence. No scheduler. No dispatcher.
# Rust exists ONLY at IO boundaries (model API, tool exec, channel send).
#
# Entry: channel adapter writes InboundMessage to "inbound" queue
# Exit: deliver_response writes to channel (Rust IO)
# Everything between is pure dataflow in .px
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# QUEUE REGISTRY (all named queues in the system)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Queue Name          | Producers                       | Consumers
# ────────────────────|─────────────────────────────────|──────────────────────
# inbound             | channel adapters (Rust IO)      | classify_and_route, track_inbound
# route_decision      | classify_and_route              | assemble_context, dispatch_steered_task
# model_request       | assemble_context,               | invoke_model
#                     | dispatch_steered_task,           |
#                     | route_model_response (tool loop) |
# model_response      | invoke_model                    | route_model_response, detect_commitments
# delivery            | route_model_response            | deliver_response
# delivered           | deliver_response                | (terminal — observability only)
# commitment_events   | detect_and_store_commitments    | (terminal — task creation done inline)
# inbound_tracked     | track_inbound                   | (terminal — history write done inline)
# heartbeat_tick      | heartbeat timer (Rust IO)       | evaluate_dispatch
# dispatch_decision   | evaluate_dispatch               | (Rust IO: TaskDispatcher)
# task_dispatch       | steer_active_task               | build_steered_prompt
# task_prompt         | build_steered_prompt            | (Rust IO: TaskDispatcher)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# IO BOUNDARIES (the ONLY Rust code that isn't pure dataflow)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Channel Adapters (telegram.rs, discord.rs, etc.)
#    - Reads: external messages
#    - Writes: InboundMessage → "inbound" queue
#    - Reads: DeliveryRequest from "delivery" queue
#    - Sends: message to external channel
#
# 2. Model Client (router.rs → RouterModelClient)
#    - Reads: ModelRequest from "model_request" queue
#    - Calls: model API (HTTP)
#    - Writes: ModelResponse → "model_response" queue
#
# 3. Tool Executor (executor.rs)
#    - Reads: tool_calls from route_model_response
#    - Executes: shell, file, network operations
#    - Writes: tool results back into model_request (tool loop)
#
# 4. Heartbeat Timer (heartbeat.rs)
#    - Fires: periodically
#    - Writes: tick → "heartbeat_tick" queue
#
# 5. TaskDispatcher (task_executor.rs)
#    - Reads: DispatchDecision from "dispatch_decision" or "task_prompt"
#    - Calls: EventSpine::emit_inbound_message (injects into "inbound")
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PROCEDURE FILES (implementations)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# unified-router.px      → classify_and_route, assemble_context, dispatch_steered_task,
#                           invoke_model, route_model_response, deliver_response,
#                           detect_and_store_commitments, track_inbound
# task-steering.px       → classify_continuation, steer_active_task
# commitment-detection.px → detect_commitments, create_tasks_from_commitments
# autonomous-dispatch.px → evaluate_dispatch, build_steered_prompt
# heartbeat-logic.px     → process_heartbeat_check
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LIFECYCLE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Startup:
#   1. PluresDB loads all .px files → registers procedures in DataflowGraph
#   2. Queues are created for every `from "X"` and `into "Y"` binding
#   3. Channel adapters start listening (Telegram, Discord, etc.)
#   4. Heartbeat timer starts firing ticks
#
# Steady state:
#   Message arrives → channel adapter writes to "inbound" → graph runs to quiescence
#   All queues empty = idle
#   Next message = next run
#
# Shutdown:
#   Channel adapters stop → no new writes to "inbound" → graph quiesces naturally
#   In-flight model calls complete or timeout
#   State is in PluresDB (persistent)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHAT THE CEREBELLUM BECOMES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# The 1100-line cerebellum/mod.rs is replaced by:
#   - classify_and_route (entry point — 60 lines of .px)
#   - assemble_context (context assembly — 50 lines of .px)
#   - Rust IO: embed_text, recall_memories (thin wrappers around PluresLM)
#
# What survives in Rust:
#   - CerebellumActionHandler: dispatches actions from .px to actual IO
#     - model_complete → ModelClient.chat()
#     - embed_text → PluresLM.embed()
#     - recall_memories → PluresLM.recall()
#     - channel_send → Telegram/Discord API
#     - dispatch_tools → ToolRegistry.execute()
#   - DataflowBridge: pushes initial datum, runs graph, reads output
#   - AuthorizationGate: stays as Rust (security boundary — never .px)
#
# What dies:
#   - router.rs (Rust heuristic routing) → replaced by classify_and_route
#   - classifier.rs (Rust intent classification) → replaced by classify_intent action
#   - context_manager.rs (Rust context window) → replaced by manage_context action
#   - pipeline.rs → the graph IS the pipeline
#   - invoke.rs → replaced by invoke_model procedure
#   - Most of mod.rs → the dataflow graph replaces imperative orchestration
